            . The officer showed me a goat, which I knew was my master's - I know nothing of the prisoner.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went after a situation at a varnish-maker's, in Liverpool-road; I was to go on Saturday for an answer - I thought I would go and cut two turfs; a man in the field asked who the goat belonged to; some men said they did not know; he then asked me if I would earn sixpence or a shilling, and take the goat with him - he called the goat, and it came; he took hold of it, put a string round it, and told me to lead it - he walked on, and went away.</p>
